definition.value: A pyridinecarbaldehyde that is pyridine-5-carbaldehyde bearing methyl, hydroxy and hydroxymethyl substituents at positions 2, 3 and 4 respectively.
An indolyl alcohol that is ethanol substituted by a 1H-indol-3-yl group at position 2.
A molecular entity that can transfer ("donate") an electron, a pair of electrons, an atom or a group to another molecular entity.
A deoxyketohexose phosphate consisting of L-rhamnulose having a monophosphate group at the 1-position.
